# v1.9.2 : fix Collection.AddStringsAsync race and CastAny Result test expectations

- #1 : `coredata/corestr/Collection.AddStringsAsync` now relies on per-item `AddLock` inside each goroutine instead of taking a single `Lock()` that was released before the goroutines ran. This eliminates the data race reported by `go test -race` in `Test_Collection_AddStringsAsync` and `Test_Collection_AddStringsAsync_CollectionBasicmethods`.
- #2 : Update `Test_CastAny_Result` and `Test_CastAny_ResultPtr` to expect successful deserialization (`hasErr: false`) now that `CastAny` correctly dispatches `Result` / `*Result` cases ahead of the `Jsoner` path (no more double-marshal).

# v1.9.1 : lint cleanup for production helpers and remaining test fixtures

- #1 : Add `//nolint:unused` directives on intentionally retained production helpers (`LinkedCollections.incrementLengthLock`, `DynamicMap.isEqualSingle`, `newBasicStringCreator.sliceNamesToMap`, `SimpleTestCase.noPrintAssert`, `FuncWrap.in/outArgsMap`, `assertDiffOnMismatch`, `reflectPath.pathName`, `reflectcore` re-exported helpers, `autofix.rxOnlyCloseParen`)
- #2 : Add blank-identifier keep-alive file in `cmd/main` so playground entry points (`readWriteTest01`, `testMakerTesting`, etc.) survive `unused` lint without modifying the placeholder `main.go`
- #3 : Suppress remaining orphan test-fixture variables in `chmodhelpertests` and `codestacktests` via `var _ = …` references

# v1.9.0 : lint root-cause cleanup for orphaned test scaffolds

- #1 : Root-cause fix — preserve intentionally retained test-case fixtures, aliases, and helpers with explicit blank-identifier references so `golangci-lint` no longer fails on orphaned coverage scaffolding
- #2 : Remove dead local `myStringer` declarations that were left behind after earlier test rewrites and never exercised by assertions

